# buzzer

Passive-buzzer driver built on top of the **ESP32 LEDC** (LED Control) peripheral.
A passive buzzer requires a PWM signal at the desired frequency; a simple
HIGH/LOW GPIO toggle does not produce sound with passive buzzers.

## Hardware connection

| Buzzer pin | ESP32-C3 GPIO |
| ---------- | ------------- |
| Signal (+) | GPIO 3        |
| GND (-)    | GND           |

## API

```c
// Configure LEDC timer 0, channel 0 for the given GPIO.  Call once at startup.
void buzzer_init(int gpio);

// Play a single tone at freq_hz for dur_ms milliseconds (blocking).
void buzzer_tone(uint32_t freq_hz, uint32_t dur_ms);

// Convenience wrappers
void buzzer_beep_short(void);         // single short beep — generic feedback
void buzzer_beep_confirm(void);       // rising two-tone  — settings saved
void buzzer_beep_cancel(void);        // low long beep    — exit without saving
void buzzer_beep_quarter(void);       // double beep      — every 15 minutes / startup
void buzzer_play_hour_melody(void);   // 7-note melody    — every full hour
```

## LEDC resource usage

| Resource        | Value          |
| --------------- | -------------- |
| LEDC timer      | LEDC_TIMER_0   |
| LEDC channel    | LEDC_CHANNEL_0 |
| Duty resolution | 8-bit          |
| Duty cycle      | 50 % (128/255) |
